.uk/resources/785028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785028/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-06","Network Rail: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) BAME people, (b) disabled people and (c) women work for Network Rail.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","111523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785029","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-14","<p>Information on the accessibility facilities available at individual stations, including step free access arrangements, is collected and held by the Rail Delivery Group and published on the National Rail Enquiries website. If any disabled passenger is unable to use a particular station the train operating company is obliged to arrange alternative transport at no additional cost.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-14T11:10:17.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785029/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785029/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785029/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-06","Railway Stations: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which railway stations do not have step-free access.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","111524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785030","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-15","<p>Information on the facilities available at railway stations is collected and held by the Rail Delivery Group, rather than the Department. However, we understand that around 460 of our 2,500 stations in the UK have step free access to and between every platform, which accounts for more than 70% of journeys. Accessibility information about individual stations is published on the National Rail Enquiries website.</p><p> </p><p>We remain committed to continuing to invest in the accessibility of the railway during the next five year Control Period from 2019 and will confirm the way in which we will deliver this later in the year.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-15T12:06:12.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785030/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785030/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-06","Railway Stations: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many railway stations (a) have and (b) do not have step-free access.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","111525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785031","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-14","<p>Network Rail’s annual profit on sale of properties since 2010 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>2016/17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Profit*</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£0.31m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£12m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£27m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£36m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£37m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£32m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£69m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£64m</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* All values are net sales income after deducting selling costs and any acquisition costs in line with Network Rail’s accounting policies.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-14T11:04:56.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785031/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785031/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-06","Network Rail: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the financial return to the public purse from the sale of Network Rail land and assets in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","111526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785032","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-16","<p>The Department does not have access to any information on the age of employees across train operating companies.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-11-16T12:25:40.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785032/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/785032/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-06","Railways: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people aged (a) under 20, (b) 21 to 30, (c) 31 to 40, (d) 41 to 50, (e) 51 to 60 and (f) over 61-years old work for each train operating company.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","111519"
